salesforcedx-einstein-gpt.walkthroughs.e: AI powered developer tool to assist with Apex and LWC programming.

It’s easy to get started with Agentforce for Developers:
- [Open a Salesforce DX Project](command:sf.project.generate)
- [Connect to a Salesforce Org](command:sf.set.default.org)
 See [Agentforce for Developers documentation](https://developer.salesforce.com/tools/vscode/en/einstein/einstein-overview) to learn more.
 __This tool uses generative AI, which can produce inaccurate or harmful responses.__
 __You can easily disable Agentforce for Developers from within Visual Studio Code. Or just disable the extension from your Extensions view.__
- [Disable Agentforce for Developers](command:salesforcedx-einstein-gpt.displayStatusMenu)
Ask Dev Assistant a question or write an instruction. You’ll receive Apex and LWC code suggestions. After you receive a response, follow up with more questions to get more accurate responses.

Use AI-based autocomplete to accept suggestions for code as you write it. Right inside your editor. These AI-generated code suggestions are context aware and are based on the metadata in your connected org.
 Inline autocompletions can be triggered in Apex and LWC (Javascript, HTML and CSS) files.

Use Agentforce for Developers to quickly generate unit tests for your Apex classes.
Let the AI know which methods to consider when generating tests. Agentforce uses the context of tests that you choose in order to create new tests that do not duplicate the code that you already have.
Open the panel to view a running history of your prompts and associated responses.
